During closing arguments, Lumka Xoxo, said their evidence could not be believed and that they had been “coached”. She described their evidence as “dramatic” and said only those children instructed to do so had taken the stand. Xoxo argued that the rapes could not have happened because there had been other people around when they allegedly took place. Molefe is facing three charges of rape and eleven of sexual assault which he allegedly committed in 2017. While giving his testimony last week, Molefe said the case against him was a plot to remove him as the security guard so that the principal Maria Mthimkhulu could be harmed because she was allegedly stealing the school’s money. 